===Etymology===

The word ''weasel'' is the direct descendant of {{etyl|ang}} ''[[weosule]]'', a weak feminine noun that has cognates in other Germanic languages (Dutch ''wezel'', German ''Wiesel''), but has no known cognates in other Indo-European languages.

